eNCA's Sport Reporter Hloni Mthimkulu has more details on this story. Courtesy #DStv403   JOHANNESBURG -Â The ANC Women's League has thrown its weight behind Ria Ledwaba, who is contesting the SAFA elections. Ledwaba, who failed to stop the election from taking place, is up against incumbent Danny Jordaan and Solly Mohlabeng for the presidency. Women's League President, Bathabile Dlamini, believes Ledwaba is being discriminated against, for being the only woman in the three-person race.